00:10:39.830 --> 00:10:43.230
both the House and the
Senate, everyone's first name,

00:10:43.230 --> 00:10:47.190
last name, state, district
number, political party,

00:10:47.190 --> 00:10:50.030
all congressional committees
on which they serve,

00:10:50.030 --> 00:10:52.280
special positions held
within those committees,

00:10:52.280 --> 00:10:53.830
and held within
Congress in general.

00:10:53.830 --> 00:10:56.800
It was more than
4,000 pieces of data

00:10:56.800 --> 00:11:01.290
that I had to have random access
to in my head like a computer.

00:11:01.290 --> 00:11:04.090
I realize that those
all seem like it

00:11:04.090 --> 00:11:06.200
extraordinary feats of memory.

00:11:06.200 --> 00:11:09.370
But in fact, it's all
just come with training.

00:11:09.370 --> 00:11:12.570
Training with techniques that
make the most efficient use

00:11:12.570 --> 00:11:15.340
of the brain to encode
information so that

00:11:15.340 --> 00:11:18.600
makes it much easier to
retrieve that information

00:11:18.600 --> 00:11:20.200
when you need it later on.

00:11:20.200 --> 00:11:22.910
Really, everyone sitting
in this room today

00:11:22.910 --> 00:11:26.750
is capable of doing absolutely
extraordinary things

00:11:26.750 --> 00:11:27.470
with your memory.

00:11:27.470 --> 00:11:29.290
You just need to learn
the right techniques

00:11:29.290 --> 00:11:31.590
and practice a little bit.

00:11:31.590 --> 00:11:34.150
My presentation will
we interactive today.

00:11:34.150 --> 00:11:37.120
I will have you go through
some exercises that

00:11:37.120 --> 00:11:40.490
may seem a bit silly or
unusual at certain points,

00:11:40.490 --> 00:11:42.990
but just bear with me,
because I promise you

00:11:42.990 --> 00:11:45.360
that what I ask
you to do is going

00:11:45.360 --> 00:11:47.530
to help you with your memory.

00:11:47.530 --> 00:11:49.620
It's going to make
it much easier

00:11:49.620 --> 00:11:51.200
for you to remember things.

00:11:51.200 --> 00:11:54.530
So everyone, please close
your eyes at this point.

00:11:54.530 --> 00:11:58.650
We will start with a warm up
visualization exercise here.

00:11:58.650 --> 00:12:01.020
You're simply going
to do your best

00:12:01.020 --> 00:12:03.540
to visualize what
I describe to you.

00:12:03.540 --> 00:12:05.620
Just do your best to
see what I describe

00:12:05.620 --> 00:12:08.740
to you happening in your mind.

00:12:08.740 --> 00:12:10.890
I want for you to
picture yourself

00:12:10.890 --> 00:12:13.120
in your current residence,
wherever you're currently

00:12:13.120 --> 00:12:13.730
living.

00:12:13.730 --> 00:12:17.270
You are in the living room
area of your residence.

00:12:17.270 --> 00:12:21.060
And you see there
standing behind podiums,

00:12:21.060 --> 00:12:24.920
looking as if they are
about to engage in a debate,

00:12:24.920 --> 00:12:28.930
you see Barack Obama
and Mitt Romney.

00:12:28.930 --> 00:12:31.840
You thought the debates
were long over in 2012,

00:12:31.840 --> 00:12:33.590
but another one's
actually about to happen

00:12:33.590 --> 00:12:35.260
in the middle of
your living room.

00:12:35.260 --> 00:12:38.890
And although this strikes
you as pretty unusual,

00:12:38.890 --> 00:12:41.960
rather than ask
any questions, you

00:12:41.960 --> 00:12:45.035
decide to simply hang back
and observe what's going on.

00:12:45.035 --> 00:12:49.360
So they begin to debate
there-- just watch this unfold.

00:12:49.360 --> 00:12:51.510
You see that the
debate is becoming

00:12:51.510 --> 00:12:54.430
more and more heated
between the two politicians,

00:12:54.430 --> 00:12:58.840
and at one point, you can
see Romney become very upset.

00:12:58.840 --> 00:13:01.860
He's visibly upset at
something that Obama says,

00:13:01.860 --> 00:13:07.410
so he reaches behind his
podium to pull out a pie.

00:13:07.410 --> 00:13:10.900
He takes this pie and
he throws it at Obama

00:13:10.900 --> 00:13:13.340
and it hits Obama
square in the face.

00:13:13.340 --> 00:13:18.630
Obama has pie splattered
all over his face.

00:13:18.630 --> 00:13:22.510
Obama is not happy
about this at all.

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:25.650
So he reaches behind his
podium now, believe it or not,

00:13:25.650 --> 00:13:27.840
to also pull out a pie.

00:13:27.840 --> 00:13:29.643
He takes it, he
throws it at Romney

00:13:29.643 --> 00:13:33.420
and it hits Romney
square in the face.

00:13:33.420 --> 00:13:37.760
What started it out as a
debate has, at this point,

00:13:37.760 --> 00:13:40.600
turned into a
full-blown pie fight.

00:13:40.600 --> 00:13:42.860
And the politicians
are continuously

00:13:42.860 --> 00:13:44.180
throwing pies at each other.

00:13:44.180 --> 00:13:45.695
Pie is flying everywhere.

00:13:49.530 --> 00:13:53.135
Just see this in your mind
to the best of your ability.

00:13:53.135 --> 00:13:55.010
The imagery doesn't need
to be crystal clear,

00:13:55.010 --> 00:13:56.690
but just see it as best you can.

00:13:59.360 --> 00:14:04.700
You are, at this point,
primarily experiencing

00:14:04.700 --> 00:14:05.690
visual images.

00:14:05.690 --> 00:14:08.640
You're seeing imagery
running through your mind.

00:14:08.640 --> 00:14:10.860
What I'd like you
to do now is attempt

00:14:10.860 --> 00:14:13.570
to involve even more senses.

00:14:13.570 --> 00:14:16.600
As you experience this scenario
happening in your mind,

00:14:16.600 --> 00:14:19.370
imagine that you cannot
only see it happening,

00:14:19.370 --> 00:14:21.420
imagine that you can hear
it happening as well.

00:14:21.420 --> 00:14:24.220
Imagine that you can hear that
pie flying through the air.

00:14:24.220 --> 00:14:27.963
You can hear the pie as it
splatters on the politicians.

00:14:33.340 --> 00:14:38.060
Imagine now that you can
eat even smell the pie.

00:14:38.060 --> 00:14:40.970
Just do your best to imagine
what that pie might smell like.

00:14:44.350 --> 00:14:45.910
Take it a step further now.

00:14:45.910 --> 00:14:49.230
Imagine that you walk up
to one of the politicians

00:14:49.230 --> 00:14:53.080
and you actually take some
of the pie off of their face.

00:14:53.080 --> 00:14:56.700
You feel in your hands--
maybe it feels sort of sticky.

00:15:01.150 --> 00:15:04.600
Go ahead now and even put
some of that pie in your mouth

00:15:04.600 --> 00:15:05.850
and taste the pie.

00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:15.200
Hopefully, you are tasting some
pie there that's pretty good.

00:15:15.200 --> 00:15:18.550
Although, some people tell
me it tastes like politician

00:15:18.550 --> 00:15:19.315
at this point.

00:15:22.430 --> 00:15:26.550
OK, go ahead and open
up your eyes everyone.

00:15:26.550 --> 00:15:28.130
Pretty easy, right?

00:15:28.130 --> 00:15:30.790
Pretty easy exercise
to complete.

00:15:30.790 --> 00:15:34.330
Some people find that
to be a fun exercise.

00:15:34.330 --> 00:15:37.500
But what does it have to do
with improving your memory?

00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:39.800
In fact, it has a
lot to do with it.

00:15:39.800 --> 00:15:42.780
If you were able to complete
that simple exercise,

00:15:42.780 --> 00:15:45.020
and I'm sure you all
were, then you actually

00:15:45.020 --> 00:15:47.090
have the ability to
remember anything

00:15:47.090 --> 00:15:51.230
at all that you would ever want
to remember, quickly, easily,

00:15:51.230 --> 00:15:54.380
and with tremendous accuracy.

00:15:54.380 --> 00:15:55.800
Here are some reasons why.

00:15:55.800 --> 00:15:57.190
Reason number one.

00:15:57.190 --> 00:16:01.400
I had you there exercise
your visualization ability.

00:16:01.400 --> 00:16:06.080
And your visual memory
is incredibly powerful.

00:16:06.080 --> 00:16:09.090
An example that I often cite in
my speeches and presentations

00:16:09.090 --> 00:16:11.220
that I now give
all over the world

00:16:11.220 --> 00:16:13.410
is a situation that
we've all experienced

00:16:13.410 --> 00:16:17.820
at some point in our life,
where you may see someone

00:16:17.820 --> 00:16:20.220
that you could
have met years ago.

00:16:20.220 --> 00:16:22.360
You could have met
them years in the past.

00:16:22.360 --> 00:16:25.610
Oftentimes, as soon as you
see that person's face,

00:16:25.610 --> 00:16:28.270
you remember their
face, you know

00:16:28.270 --> 00:16:30.080
that you've met them
somewhere before,

00:16:30.080 --> 00:16:32.560
